    <!-- Story Section -->
    <string name="story_intro">This app was born from a unique vision during my final year as a BA Sanskrit student at SNGS College, Pattambi (2022-2025).</string>
    <string name="story_unique">While my peers wrote traditional books on Mahabharata and Ramayana, I chose to do something different—something that had never been done in our college before. I built an Android app.</string>
    <string name="story_journey_title">🎯 The Journey</string>
    <string name="story_started">Started: December 2024</string>
    <string name="story_duration">Development Time: 6-7 months of learning &amp; building</string>
    <string name="story_challenges">Challenges: Late nights, health struggles, Learning Challenges</string>
    <string name="story_data_source">Data Source: Manually extracted from \'Sabda Manjari\' book</string>
    <string name="story_conclusion">My programming journey started in 10th standard with HTML/CSS, evolved through React, React Native, Flutter, and finally found its home in Kotlin. This app represents not just code, but a bridge between ancient Sanskrit wisdom and modern technology.</string>

